Downloads Steps on ubuntu:

There are two deployment mode for the openObserve: single node mode and HA mode

Go to this website: https://openobserve.ai/downloads/
Run this on the ubuntu terminal: curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openobserve/openobserve/main/downloadO2.sh | sh -s opensource v0.70.2

Download Complete

Now we can start the openObserve
export ZO_ROOT_USER_EMAIL=root@example.com
export ZO_ROOT_USER_PASSWORD=Complexpass#123
./openobserve

To make the OpenObserve a service:
sudo mkdir -p /opt/openobserve
sudo mv openobserve /opt/openobserve/
sudo chmod +x /opt/openobserve/openobserve

sudo vim /etc/systemd/system/openobserve.service

[Unit]
Description=OpenObserve Service
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
WorkingDirectory=/opt/openobserve
ExecStart=/opt/openobserve/openobserve
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

EnvironmentFile=/opt/openobserve/.env

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

sudo vim /opt/openobserve/.env

ZO_ROOT_USER_EMAIL=root@example.com
ZO_ROOT_USER_PASSWORD=Complexpass#123

sudo chmod 600 /opt/openobserve/.env

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable openobserve
sudo systemctl start openobserve
sudo systemctl status openobserve
sudo systemctl restart openobserve

To see the logs:
journalctl -u openobserve -f
sudo journalctl -u openobserve -n 200 | grep -iE "s3|flush|error|upload|compact"
sudo journalctl -u openobserve -f | grep -iE "s3|flush|compact|error|start"
